cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

The paper deals with object tracking using event cameras, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also involves robotics and machine learning techniques, which are covered by cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) respectively. The proposed method involves tracking objects in real-time, which is a problem of machine learning and optimization, and hence cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. Finally, the paper involves the use of event cameras, which are a type of neuromorphic sensors, and hence cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category.
